# Minimal diff

- Read surrounding code first; match naming, types, and patterns already in the file
- Solve the requested task only; no drive-by refactors
- Reuse existing functions and patterns before adding abstractions
- No one-line helpers that should stay inline
- No extra error handling for impossible edge cases
- New behavior needs tests first (see `tdd.mdc`); no tests that only assert the obvious
- No new markdown files unless requested
- If two approaches exist, pick the simpler one that matches the repo

When copying from MLLM-Shap, port the minimum slice needed — do not bulk-copy experiments or multimodal code unless the task requires it.
